cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DS 

The paper deals with privacy-preserving techniques for cooperative spectrum sensing, which involves wireless networks and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves the use of an additional architectural entity and cryptographic mechanisms, which suggests a possible fit with cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
